		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Unfortunately, EQ has never had the life it was promised because Verant for whatever reasons never actively evolved it. There is a difference between having a story and making it part of the game....I think its very deceptive for anyone to say EQs storyline is evolving....its not...thats like saying the moon is made of cheese its not but there are stories about it being so...EQ is a hack and slash game it is not a roleplaying game. Are there roleplayers? Yes. Are there more hak and slashers than role players? Yes. Does the game make you want to roleplay? No. People do that (hell they have to set up special servers to get people to roleplay am I not correct?) So this means that EQ is relatively static, unchanging, and just people enjoying the scenery and trying to level. Does anyone really enjoy hell levels and medding and stuff? No. <br> forexample, Is there a real reason to have Ragebringer? No. Do these new uktimate quests mean jack to the game? No. Are these items worth the effort? No. Do mainly only guilds that bully people around have them? Yes. Why? They hack and slash their way to get them. But oh well its fun to play EQ for what it is I guess...as long as you KNOW what it is you areplaying......		

