			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				I guess the trick would be how to pull this off. I really don't like to go to events where there is a well rehearsed play before you because ultimatly you get folks that are rude and ruin it for everyone.  <br> One of the funniest thangs happen the other day when a we get system messages of a terrible storm at sea.  Followed up a little later with an ooc that the boats were down for a bit.  <br> Just a thought but what would really be wrong with a system message that came along with the story then maybe adding something for fun.   <br> Say for example The Cyclops (insert name) is angry and has summoned up friends to push the invaders out of Rath Mtn with his trusted (insert special item)  Now those that want can go try and kill him and his bodys.   <br> You could also do something were a so and so wizzard has lost something he leaves a clue and if you figure it out and retrive the item and bring it to him they you get a reward even if its just exp.   <br> If you do these with a story in mind you can drop little tid bits until you reach a climax.  Just a thought I know I would enjoy.  		

