		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Many of the NPCs in the game have a background history that you can ask them (or others) about. However, because of Faction many NPCs in the game are not going to talk to you, so its unlikely you'll be able to get the full picture without resorting to secondary characters or the web. <br>  <br> The way the game is designed, with static spawns, fixed loot tables and set-in-stone zone architecture, makes it hard for them to implement an evolving storyline. Only a couple of times have they dramatically changed the NPCs in a whole zone (Split Paw, Kithicor). AFAIK they have never changed the architecture. <br>  <br> Storywise the best they can do, therefore, is GM events where one or two GM controlled NPCs will enact a little scene and maybe spawn a few monsters in the process. Mostly these scenes are unrelated and have no lasting impact on the game, which thus remains as it was before, hack n' slash. <br>  <br> What I'd have liked is High Pass overrun by Orcs or Gnolls, Freeport burned to the ground with refugee camps in North Ro, new Guard towers being raised (and old ones ruined) in the Karanas, and so on; but for those kind of changes you have to play AC or presumably one of the upcoming MMORPGs. <br> 		

